# Sandbox Directory Structure

All game content lives under `sandbox/src/`. **Never** add game logic to `viberanium/`.

## Layout

```
sandbox/src/
├── SandboxApp.tsx          # package entry re-export only
├── catalog/                # declarative data — lists, maps, registries (no spawn logic)
│   ├── types/              # LevelDefinition, SkeletalCharacterDef shapes
│   ├── assets/             # glTF/texture URL constants
│   ├── animations/         # anim pack + clip name maps (e.g. kaykitMedium)
│   ├── characters/         # SkeletalCharacterDef entries
│   ├── levels/             # level spawn data + LEVEL_CATALOG registry
│   ├── keys/               # GAME_COMPONENT_KEYS, attachment tag maps
│   └── ui/                 # theme tokens (loading colors, etc.)
├── entities/               # factories, components, systems
│   ├── actor/              # shared skeletal spawn pipeline
│   ├── player/             # createPlayer, playerController, input system
│   └── enemies/            # robot, combatMech, dummy + testAi
├── scenes/
│   └── common/             # createPlayableScene, useLevelScene, ground, prop
├── globals/                # bootstrap, sceneManager (session autoloads)
├── menus/                  # standalone React overlays (performance menu, …)
└── ui/
    ├── app/                # SandboxApp shell
    └── theme/              # style.css + design tokens
```

## Catalog rule

A file belongs in `catalog/` when it is **primarily declarative data** consumed elsewhere:

| Belongs in `catalog/` | Belongs outside `catalog/` |
|-----------------------|----------------------------|
| URL/path constants | `loadSkeletalCharacter`, `spawnActor` |
| `Record<id, Definition>` maps | `installTestAiSystem` |
| Clip name maps | `createPlayer` |
| `SkeletalCharacterDef` instances | `instantiateProp` |
| `GAME_COMPONENT_KEYS` | Component `createX()` factories |
| Level spawn layouts | Scene `load()` / `unload()` |

`catalog/` may import `catalog/*` and `viberanium` types. **`catalog/` must not import from `entities/`, `scenes/`, or `globals/`.**

Engine `COMPONENT_KEYS` stays in `viberanium`. Sandbox-specific keys live in `catalog/keys/components.ts`.

## Entity rule

| Folder | Role |
|--------|------|
| `entities/actor/` | `loadSkeletalCharacter`, `spawnSkeletalCharacter`, `spawnActor`, `buildKaykitMediumDef` |
| `entities/player/` | `createPlayer`, player components + `installPlayerInputSystem` |
| `entities/enemies/<kind>/` | `createRobot`, `createCombatMech`, … + shared `components/`, `systems/` |

New enemies follow `entities/enemies/spider/` with `createSpider.ts`, `components/`, `systems/`.

## Scenes rule

- `scenes/common/createPlayableScene.ts` — installs scene systems once; `load()` / `unload()` lifecycle
- `scenes/common/useLevelScene.ts` — maps `LevelDefinition` → playable scene
- `scenes/common/prop.ts` — `instantiateProp` (static glTF prop spawn factory; **not** catalog)
- `scenes/common/ground.ts` — ground mesh for render pipeline

Per-level custom logic: add `scenes/<levelId>/` only when catalog data is insufficient.

## Globals rule

`globals/bootstrap.ts` and `globals/sceneManager.ts` are session composition only — no entity factories, no level spawn data.

## UI / menus rule

- `ui/app/SandboxApp.tsx` — React shell; imports `globals/bootstrap`
- `menus/` — overlay components (e.g. `menus/performance/PerformanceMenu.tsx`)
- Master CSS: `ui/theme/style.css`; feature CSS colocated with components

## Forbidden

- Barrel `index.ts` anywhere under `sandbox/src/`
- Catalog files with registry writes or `install*System`
- `startup/`, `levels/`, `character/`, `npcs/`, `world/` paths (removed — use structure above)
- Component key strings outside `catalog/keys/` (except `viberanium` `COMPONENT_KEYS`)
- `staticProps.ts` — use `scenes/common/prop.ts` + `instantiateProp`
